==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inanimation
<hw>In*an`i*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 2d
<er>Inanimate</er>.]</ety> <def>Lack of animation; lifeless;
dullness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inanimation</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inanimation
<hw>In*an`i*ma"tion</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 1st
<er>Inanimate</er>.]</ety> <def>Infusion of life or vigor; animation;
inspiration.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>inanimation</qex> of Christ living and breathing within
us.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inanitiate</ent>⟦br⟧
